<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Industry" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Industry,</orth> assiduity, zealous activity: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 4, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.328" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 328</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 5, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.31" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 1, 63</bibl>. Not quite intelligibly used by Armado: <cit><quote>thine in the dearest design of i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 88</bibl></cit> (== earnestness?).
